*.tmp
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
infra/runtime/

# --- Private working material ---
# Present on disk for local development; deliberately NOT tracked and never
# published from this repo. This is the publication boundary: everything below
# is the private corpus / planning / agent-harness / mirror machinery. A fresh
# `git add -A` will not stage any of it.
/.agents/
/.claude/
/.codex/
/.cursor/
/.grok/
# .github is private EXCEPT the public CI workflow (git can only re-include a
# child if its parent dirs aren't wholly excluded — hence the pattern ladder):
/.github/*
!/.github/workflows
/.github/workflows/*
!/.github/workflows/public-ci.yml
/.githooks/
/.dockerignore
/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md
/ARCHITECTURE.md
/LESSONS.md
/docs/
/planning/
/publication/
/tools/scripts/verify-publication.mjs
/packages/testkit/fixtures/corpus-manifest.synthetic.json
